## Required Output Format

Output ONLY the following XML block. Do NOT include preamble, commentary, or markdown code fences.

```xml
<fitness_evaluation>
  <score>3</score>
  <rationale>The synthesis addresses the drivers aspect of the question well (claims C1-C4) but largely omits solutions, which the question explicitly asks about. Source r1_s03 has no representation despite providing unique perspectives on mitigation strategies. The uncertainties section captures some gaps but misses the methodological limitations flagged by r1_s04.</rationale>
  <suggestions>
    <suggestion>Add claims from r1_s03 and r1_s04 on solutions/mitigation strategies — the question asks about both drivers and solutions</suggestion>
    <suggestion>Source r1_s03 is entirely unrepresented; incorporate their perspective on adaptive management approaches</suggestion>
  </suggestions>
</fitness_evaluation>
```

### ⚠️ CRITICAL CONSTRAINTS

- **Output ONLY the `<fitness_evaluation>` XML block.** No preamble, no markdown fences, no commentary.
- **`<score>` must be an integer from 1-5** (use the Score Conversion table in the rubric above).
- **`<rationale>` must reference claim IDs and source IDs** when identifying issues.
- **Each `<suggestion>` must be actionable** — cite the specific claim IDs and what to change.

